  "body": "\r\n***Type***: Bug\r\n\r\n***Summary***: It was reproduced twice on the contact who recovered an account but updated the name and profile after his contact request been submitted. Not always reproducible, but see the steps below\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nUsername and userpic of contact who sent a contact request kept updated\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nUsername/userpic drop to default for who received contact request from recovered account even he updated profile data\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n- Open Status on Device 1 and Device 2\r\n- Device 1 creates new account (Contact 1)\r\n- Device 2 recovers an existing account (note: in this case there are default username and userpic)\r\n- Both contacts join the same public chat (e.g. `reproduceme`)\r\n- Contact 1 sends a message in the public chat\r\n- Contact 2 taps on profile icon of Contact 1 \r\n- Contact 2 taps 'Add to Contacts' followed by 'Send a message'. (Note: on this stage Contact2 navigated to 1-1 chat with Contact 1)\r\n- Contact 1 navigated to 1-1 chat initiated with him by Contact2\r\n- Contact 1 sends a text message (e.g. `Who are you my friend?`)\r\n- Contact 2 updates profile username and picture to non-default\r\n- Contact 1 checks on his side if the profile data of the Contact 2\r\n- In a case of previous step is OK - Contact 1 moves on background and back to foreground \r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: Release 0.9.21 (9th release)\r\n* Operating System:  iOS (so far) but Android likely affected as well.\r\n\r\n#### Logs\r\n\r\nTF session for one instance starts from 11:00 - see there first updated contact details then during 2-3 seconds app moved background-foreground and contact data updated to default https://app.testfairy.com/projects/4803590-status/builds/8503790/sessions/4394611520/?accessToken=v1u1PlDa7PpGJmxvhQTQd9nxqw0\n\n<blockquote><div><strong><a href=\"https://app.testfairy.com/projects/4803590-status/builds/8503790/sessions/4394611520/?accessToken=v1u1PlDa7PpGJmxvhQTQd9nxqw0\">TestFairy: Status 0.9.21 (6106) @2018</a></strong></div></blockquote>",
